A vintage 1970s-style illustration of a towering mountain of discarded electronics—old monitors, circuit boards, tangled cables, and defunct machinery—rendered in muted olive greens, burnt oranges, and harvest golds with grainy paper texture. In the foreground, a single delicate seedling pushes through a cracked motherboard, its tiny green leaves vibrant against the faded technological debris. The composition uses a cross-section view reminiscent of retro educational posters, with warm halftone dot patterns and slightly faded edges suggesting an aged print quality.
